{"key":"processedPost-9451286","value":{"id":9451286,"first":9398105,"last":9467340,"when":1229560718,"utime":"12/18/08 02:38 AM","content":"Don't put a humidifier in a terrarium.&nbsp; You can put one in a mini-greenhouse, but it's too easy to humidify a terrarium with perlite.&nbsp; Besides, fresh air exchange is FAR more important than soaking the hell out of your cakes.&nbsp; I'd recommend the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium</a>.&nbsp; It takes care of itself and all you need to do is mist.<br />RR","title":"Re: humidification","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}